entry.title: Two Cyclones Hit Days Apart. Can Scientists Prove Climate Change Caused Them?

entry.title: Bill Richardson, Former New Mexico Governor and U.N. Ambassador, Dies at 75
entry.content: The Democrat also served as energy secretary for Bill Clinton and had aspired to be the country’s first Hispanic president.

entry.title: In New Moon Race, Russian Crash Shows the Chief U.S. Rival Is China
entry.content: Like the scramble to plant boots on the moon in the 1960s, the race to establish a base there is a contest between the world’s superpowers.
